Description: Ostracon, fragment of the body of a red-brown pottery ribbed vessel, the fabric is partially grey in section, the exterior is covered with a cream-coloured slip and very faint traces of at least four lines of black-painted demotic text.
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (393770) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/393770)
